    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR2o0001-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-h.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:00:35.715+09:00">3. Doubting the old</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:12:57.557+09:00">The tasks of the historians in antiquity</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:02:18.848+09:00">were divided in two:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:04:24.17+09:00">one was to record the words (that were spoken)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:10:07.419+09:00">the other was to record the actions.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:13:46.43+09:00">However, the learning of the scholars of antiquity </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:24:04.718+09:00">was focused on the words.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T19:19:40.247+09:00">For example: of the rules of Yu and Xia,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:51:05.093+09:00">the decrees of the Shang and Zhou,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:51:20.827+09:00">the words of Zhong Hui and Zhou Ren</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:53:23.996+09:00">and the discourses of Shi Yi and Zang Wen</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T19:38:19.373+09:00">all the speeches of wandering orators, responses of foreign envoys, advice or written suggestions to a ruler,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T19:41:43.443+09:00">there is none that is not quoted</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T19:41:50.202+09:00">or returned to as a model.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T19:43:17.516+09:00">For the (records of) actions, things did not go that way.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T20:06:59.249+09:00">Shao Hao named his officials after birds,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T20:07:32.521+09:00">Yao Tang tamed dragons in order to be appointed to an official position,</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
